text.response:
O God! Thou art my God alone;
No idol rivals thee in might,
No shadow claims what thou hast sown,
No dawn supplants thy holy light.
The world in splendor tempts my eye,
Yet none can woo me from thy side;
Thy mercy vast as ocean sky,
Thy truth the star by which I bide.
All fleeting joys, to dust are blown;
Eternal King, thou art my own.
